    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Intake, Inlet, and Exhaust Manifolds -
        Cleaning and Inspection
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Cleaning and Inspection</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="1">
            <title>Exhaust Manifold</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean exhaust manifold thoroughly with a suitable non-caustic solvent. Scrape off excess
                    scale and rust from manifold surfaces.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After cleaning, blow dry using filtered
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_1.xml" xrefid="Safety10" appearance="hottext">compressed air</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check manifold for cracks and damage. Replace manifold as necessary.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check for warpage as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install exhaust manifold without the gasket to a cleaned cylinder head mating
                        surface. Torque 12 mounting bolts (M12 x 35) to the
                        <hotlnk document="eges2651_60.xml" xrefid="t03002" appearance="hottext">special torque
                            value</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f2650308" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../figH14/H14013.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                        <caption>Checking exhaust manifold for cracks and warpage</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Use a 0.25 mm (0.010 in) feeler gauge to measure the gap between the mating surfaces
                        of the manifold and engine. If the feeler gauge passes through the gap, the manifold must be
                        resurfaced.
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>A maximum of 0.64 mm (0.025 in) of material can be ground off to correct warpage.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove 12 bolts (M12 x 35) and manifold.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If the warpage cannot be corrected by grinding manifold mating surface, replace
                        manifold.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
